title: For Sale:  SKS Paratrooper
postcontent:
This is the shorter barreled, less common SKS Paratrooper model.  This one was made by Norinco and imported by K-Sports Imports (KSI) in 1994.  I purchased it new at that time and it's probably had about 300 or so rounds of 7.62X39 through it in those 20+ years.  The SKS Paratrooper makes a handy package with it's shorter barrel (16” versus the 20” on the standard SKS).
At the time of purchase, new SKS rifles had to be sold without bayonets, so one is not included with this model.  This model features a milled trigger guard/housing and a threaded barrel and all serial numbers match (receiver, receiver cover, magazine, trigger guard, bolt, and bolt carrier).
The appearance of this gun is typical of a Norinco SKSs from the era, which means somewhat hasty bluing and stock finish.  So even though this gun has been used very little, cosmetically it's somewhat rough.  Included with the gun are the original box, instruction manual, tool/cleaning kit, cleaning rod, oil bottle, and sling.
$525 Firm

title: For Sale:  PRICE DROP & OPTIONS ADDED - MP5 Clone (semi-auto) from German Parts Kit
postcontent: MP5 Clone built with German parts kit + 3 LE/MIL marked mags + 3 HK mags + MP-5 Armorers Instruction Manual = $2200 (shipping to FFL extra, FTF in Louisville free).Following the sale of the MP5 clone. German A3 collapsible stock for $125 (if purchased and you are going to use the A3 stock to make an SBR, you must be keep in seperate location until stamp has been obtained, stock will ship from Arkansas to buyer as I do not have it in my possession).In 2001 I had the opportunity to train with an MP5. I loved this platform and wanted to get one for myself. Well, not being able to buy (or afford to buy) a real MP5 I decided to build one for myself. I did extensive research and purchased an A2 parts kit with a pistol end cap from Adam at HKParts.net. Adam referred me to Jeff at Parabellum Combat Systems (Jeff is fantastic, check the HKpro.com board for comments regarding his work) for advice on building my MP5. After several conversations with Jeff, I was quick to determine that building this platform in my garage was a little out of my league. I called Jeff and he mentioned that if I was ever in Oklahoma I could stop by the shop and he would help me with the build. A couple months later I was able to setup up a trip to Oklahoma to meet with Jeff. Once in the shop Jeff had me place the US made flat into the bending jig and bend it using his shops press. Once I had bent the flat to shape, Jeff finished the process (welding, placement and alignment of parts, etc) over the next few weeks and transferred the platform to me. I was able to purchase 6 curved, 30 round mags (3 have HK restricted markings on them) and run about 1000 rounds of 9 mm through it over the next several months. The platform ran beautifully and was a blast to shoot. It’s been stored in a humidity control safe for the last 12 years or so, as I have not had a lot of time to shoot it. You can by a demilled MP5 parts kit for around $1790, 6 magazines at $45 to $75 each, flat and parts kit for around $200 and have a reputable builder put it together for you for an additional $1400 (the builder is key if you want a great platform). So, for around $3600 you can have an MP5 clone from a German parts kit or you can consider this already built platform for $2200. So what do you get for the $$$? A completely built MP5 clone pistol that has the following: •HK 3-Lug MP5 Barrel - cold hammer forged •Cocking Tube •Front Sight Tower •Wide Fore arm - Black •Bolt Group - MP5 Full Auto •2 small and 1 large Push Pin •3 - 30 Round Curved Magazines - Genuine HK •3 - 30 Round Curved Magazines – HK•Rear Sight Assembly •Pistol End Cap •MP5 Sling •Manual •Trigger Group (modified to semi-auto only) It would not take much effort or dollars to make this into a really cool MP5 rifle. Weld on a fake suppressor (US Made MP5 3-lug barrel extension, Fake suppressor from HKparts.net) and add an A3 collapsing stock and you have a really cool looking platform. I am not in a “have to sell” situation and am not interested in any trades or offers at this time. You must legally be able to purchase a gun/rifle/pistol in order to buy this MP5 clone. FTF in Middletown, KY is perferable (must be willing to provide proof of KY residency). I will ship to an FFL at your expense. FFL must be willing to accept item from non-FFL.

postcontent: I have a like new PSA AR 15 16in Stainless Dissipator upper with Magpul forend, PSA Moultrie lower with enhanced polished trigger Magpul stock grip and trigger guard, heavy buffer, colt full auto BCG and magpul flip up rear sight. 200 rounds fired through this weapon with no issues. Will sell for 750 or best offer or trade for quality firearms. Will include 1 meatal 30 round mag. REDACTED. Here is the info on the upper Once upon a time, a "dissipator" AR was created by taking a 20" rifle-length gas system upper and cutting the barrel down to 16". This allowed the shooter to keep the long sight radius of a rifle for accuracy, but keep the carbine length barrel for maneuverability. The proximity of the gas port to the muzzle, however, played havoc with timing and made reliability a hit or miss proposition. Advances in AR technology have produced reliable carbine and mid-length gas systems, that can be hidden using low-profile gas blocks. This allows for a front sight base to be pinned in the rifle position for the longer sight radius without the worry of the unorthodox gas port location affecting operation. We use the term "mock" to differentiate our dissipator from a cut-down rifle length version. Barrel: 416 Stainless steel. Chambered in 5.56 NATO, with a 1/7 twist, M4 barrel extension, and a mid-length gas system. Barrel is is finished off with a MOE M-Lok rifle-length handguard, F-Marked gas sight base, and A2 flash hider.Upper: Forged 7075-T6 A3 AR upper is made to MIL-SPECS and hard coat anodized black for durability. Featuring machined T marks, and a mil-spec finish. These uppers are made for us right here in the USA by a mil-spec manufacturer.
